    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mince is browning, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
